OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41103
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1780427468
OL,3,CThousands still have 'intermittent
OL,4,Csupplies' as drinking water returns
OL,6,FIn a statement, Mr Beaton said:
OL,7,F"Drinking water supplies have returned
OL,8,Ffor all customers impacted by the
OL,9,Fwater supply interruptions in Kent
OL,10,Fcaused by exceptionally high demand,
OL,11,Ffollowing the period of hot weather.
OL,13,F"However, a burst water main in
OL,14,FWhitstable has caused customers in the
OL,15,Fimmediate area to lose supply or have
OL,16,Flow water pressure. We are working to
OL,17,Fhave these customers back in supply as
OL,18,Fquickly as possible.
OL,26,@oD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G3/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41104
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1780427468
OL,3,CThousands still have 'intermittent
OL,4,Csupplies' as drinking water returns
OL,6,F"Although our network is continuing to
OL,7,Frecover, levels of drinking water in
OL,8,Four storage tanks across Kent are
OL,9,Fstill low and we are asking customers
OL,10,Fto use water for essential purposes
OL,11,Fonly - drinking, cooking, and hygiene.
OL,12,FWe are continuing to use our tankers
OL,13,Fto support the network and aid
OL,14,Frecovery.
OL,26,@nD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G4/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41105
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1780427468
OL,3,CThousands still have 'intermittent
OL,4,Csupplies' as drinking water returns
OL,6,F"Across Kent in the Coxheath, Headcorn
OL,7,Fand Ulcombe areas, there are still
OL,8,Fapproximately 2,220 customers
OL,9,Fexperiencing intermittent supplies
OL,10,Fwhile we continue to stabilise the
OL,11,Fnetwork, but this is an improving
OL,12,Fpicture.
OL,14,F"We are continuing to do everything we
OL,15,Fcan to get treated water into our
OL,16,Fdrinking water storage tanks,
OL,17,Fincluding using our fleet of tankers
OL,18,Fto support the network and ensure all
OL,19,Favailable treatment works are running
OL,20,Fat full capacity.
OL,26,@nD@AOUvD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G5/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41106
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1780427468
OL,3,CThousands still have 'intermittent
OL,4,Csupplies' as drinking water returns
OL,6,FMr Benton continued: "We are sincerely
OL,7,Fsorry to customers for the disruption
OL,8,Fto their water supply and know how
OL,9,Ffrustrating it is, especially in hot
OL,10,Fweather.
OL,12,F"We have delivered water to schools in
OL,13,Faffected areas today to ensure they
OL,14,Fcould open as planned, and continue to
OL,15,Fwork closely with the schools and Kent
OL,16,FCounty Council.
OL,26,@nD@VOUtD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41107
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1780427468
OL,3,CThousands still have 'intermittent
OL,4,Csupplies' as drinking water returns
OL,6,F"In areas where there has been a
OL,7,Fsupply interruption - or where we
OL,8,Fbelieve issues may continue to occur -
OL,9,Fwe're delivering bottled water to
OL,10,Fcustomers on our Priority Services
OL,11,FRegister.
OL,13,F"We have delivered more than half a
OL,14,Fmillion litres of bottled water to
OL,15,Fcustomers on our Priority Services
OL,16,FRegister and also delivered bottled
OL,17,Fwater to critical care settings such
OL,18,Fas care homes, GP surgeries,
OL,19,Fpharmacies and dentists.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/9
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,412,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41108
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F411A1780427468
OL,3,CThousands still have 'intermittent
OL,4,Csupplies' as drinking water returns
OL,6,F"We have been working 24/7 with our
OL,7,Ffleet of tankers to support our
OL,8,Fnetwork where demand has been
OL,9,Fextremely high. So far, we have
OL,10,Ftankered over 2,998,181 litres of
OL,11,Fwater into the network.
OL,13,F"We have also given out more than 1.1
OL,14,Fmillion litres of water at our bottled
OL,15,Fwater stations across Kent."
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOU
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G8/9
